nd into the realm of popular politics—on the Knesset floor, in the media, in shopping malls, and on the streets. Included for the first time is the dataset for the author's national survey of women's movement volunteers.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aJudicial reviewxIsraelxIsrael. 0aJudicial reviewzIsrael. 0aPolitical questions and judicial powerxIsrael. 0aPolitical questions and judicial powerzIsrael. 4aArea Studies : Israel Studies. 4aCriminology : Criminology. 4aCultural Studies : Cultural Studies. 4aGender and Sexuality : Gender Studies. 4aPolitics and Law : Comparative Politics. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Comparative Politics.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143846208040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438462080423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438462080/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles